  gameplaySummary: An aggressive invasive colony that uses cool, moist habitat, defends
    its enclosed nest, and creates high-pressure territory contests.
  ecologicalRole: Creates high ecological pressure through aggressive defence and
    competition in suitable habitat.
  nestType: Commonly underground or enclosed rather than an exposed Polistes comb.
  habitatCue: Cooler, moister, river, irrigated, or human-modified habitat.
  threatResponse: High aggression with strong nest defence, chasing, and a shorter
    reaction window.
  learningLesson: Environmental conditions and nest architecture are important identification
    evidence.
